    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-12T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-12T09:00:00-05:00" n="952"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d952">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5611/7–1254: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Deputy United States Representative at the United
                        Nations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WADSWORTHJJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">official use only</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-12T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 12, 1954—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. From <persName corresp="#p_SEARSM1">Sears</persName> for <persName
                        corresp="#p_KEYDMK1">Key</persName>. In view importance clearly favorable
                    vote three-power resolution Marshall Islanders petition, consider it essential
                    that Department take appropriate steps to assure affirmative vote El Salvador
                    and Haiti. It is not expected that any of three draft resolutions will receive
                    majority vote in petitions committee. Thus all three expected to come before
                        <gloss target="#t_TC1">TC</gloss> for action by Wednesday, July 14. <pb
                        facs="1538" n="1510" xml:id="pg_1510"/> If affirmative vote El Salvador and
                    Haiti received, expect favorable vote three-power draft nine-three (<gloss
                        target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>, India, Syria).<note n="1" xml:id="d952fn1"
                        >For the voting, both in the Standing Committee on Petitions and in the
                        Trusteeship Council itself, see <persName corresp="#p_GERIGOB1"
                            >Gerig</persName> memorandum of July 26, 1954, <hi rend="italic"
                            >infra</hi>.</note> [<persName corresp="#p_SEARSM1"
                    >Sears</persName>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WADSWORTHJJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
